content:
Customize the appearance and behavior of OmniScript elements and Card layouts using the Vlocity Newport Design System. 
Newport includes Storybook.js, a browser-based preview tool that enables you to see your changes in action.

System requirements:

Git (git-scm documentation)
nodeJS v12.0 or higher (Node documentation)
Gulp CLI: npm install --global gulp-cli

To install Newport and brand OmniScripts and Cards:

Clone vlocityinc/newport-design-system from https://github.com/vlocityinc/newport-design-system using a command-line interface.
Perform the latest steps to install the correct dependencies.
Launch the Storybook.js preview by issuing the command npm start.
Review the documentation in the Storybook preview.

To customize the appearance of your OmniScripts or FlexCards, edit the CSS and HTML files in the UI subdirectory of the directory where you cloned Newport.

Apply modifications to the Newport design system by adding a Static Resource that overrides the Newport theme wherever it is available. Once uploaded, the Newport changes are applied to any OmniScripts using Newport.

Before Vlocity Spring '19, make your style changes available in OmniScript's Preview mode using Visualforce.
title: Branding OmniScripts and Cards with Vlocity Newport Design System
